{
 "name": "RPlog_SW1_Log_2000-06-25",
 "title": "Brooding in the Mess Hall",
 "summary": "In the mess hall of the NRSC Deliverance, General Arands arrives irritated, shaking off the NRI \"shadow\" assigned to dog him, and relaxes among his squadron pilots over his favorite Tralusian leaf tea. The surly Bazil McKenzie storms in and downs a triple shot of Corellian Blood Vodka, loudly cursing the Intelligence officers who have ransacked his quarters over the murder charge of which he was already acquitted, even stabbing his datapad with a vibroknife in disgust. The green cadet Vek Eldar cautiously strikes up conversation with the brooding McKenzie and fetches him strong caf, while Arands, his XO Lelila Jayespyer, and the pilot Avitar trade easy talk about the flood of new cadets, replacing lost squadron mates, and a strike against the Imperials that Arands hints is brewing. As Vek drifts over to introduce himself to the general, the still-fuming Bazil settles his tab and slinks off to sleep.",
 "rows": [
